<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-124-144 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 916 530</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  June 24 1991 v25 n25 p88(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Portable speed, security, color at issue.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Slater, Derek.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Portable computers are becoming much more popular choices overdesktop microcomputers because of their increased speed, colormonitors with clearer displays and better security features thatprotect important data.andP;  Although vendors are having somedifficulty getting 80386SX notebooks into the marketplace,i486-based notebooks are scheduled to be shipped in June 1991.andO;There have been some complaints about the cost, weight and lowquality of color LCD displays, but Toshiba America InformationSystems Inc and Modgraph Inc have both been working on the qualityissue.andP;  Toshiba introduced the T3200XC in Mar 1990, which usesthin-film transistor technology to create higher readability,while Modgraph introduced the first portable with 256-color UltraVideo Graphics Array display.andP;  Trackballs are also becomingincreasingly popular in laptops with the future possibility ofusing graphical user interfaces.andP;  The security of storingsensitive data can be solved one way by using a disk that acts asa key to the system.andP;  Personal Computer Card Corp's Lapguardrequires a user to enter a 3 1/2 inch floppy disk into theportable and enter a password.andP;  If access is tried without theproper disk, the computer locks the screen.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Toshiba America Information Systems Inc. (Products)Modgraph Inc. (Products)Personal Computer Card Corp. (Products).andO;Topic:     Portable computersCompetitionMicrocomputersData securityTrackballsDisplays.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>